<div id="wb_element_instance203" class="wb_element" style=" line-height: normal;"><h3 class="wb-stl-heading3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>PUERTO MADRYN 4 days, 3 nights</strong></h3>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"> </h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>The program includes the following services:</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>* At Puerto Madryn: Lodging at the chosen hotel with breakfast.<br>
* Transfers Airport / Hotel / Airport.<br>
* Traditional Excursion to Peninsula de Valdez.</strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><br><strong>Day 1: BUENOS AIRES / PUERTO MADRYN</strong></h2>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"> </h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong>From the Airport of the City of Buenos Aires you will embark toward the Patagonia. You will step Puerto Madryn, area of Frank Whales and of frank winds. Transfer to the selected hotel. The rest of the day is free. According to your flight time, you will be able to take advantage to carry out some activity or trip. The Submarine Baptism would be a great experience of Diving in the Argentinean Sea. At night a walk for the coast will define the infinite on the sea.</strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"> </h2>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Day 2: PUERTO MADRYN</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Breakfast. Today you begin to palpitate the steppe patagónica. . . and their fauna. For that reason you will leave toward Peninsula of Valdes, knowing Puerto Pirámides. In this day we suggest you to add to the program the Avistaje of Whales, unique and surprising. In the afternoon the sun goes hiding in the plateau, while you return to Puerto Madryn. Lodging in the hotel.</strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Day 3: PUERTO MADRYN</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Breakfast. The day is totally free, but that is not what we suggest you! There is a variety of trips to carry out like visiting Punta Tombo's Penguins, one of the most important reservations in the world. At night lodging in the hotel.</strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"> </h2>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Day 4: PUERTO MADRYN / BUENOS AIRES</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"> </h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Breakfast. Transfer to the Puerto Madryn Airport to return to Buenos Aires. Arrive to Buenos Aires City.</strong></h1>

